{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NhqDjqsD1sQ4WcYbGUcYZM","type":"tool_result","content":"variable\tvalue\tdescription\nadmission.disk_bandwidth_tokens.elastic.enabled\ttrue\twhen true, and provisioned bandwidth for the disk corresponding to a store is configured, tokens for elastic work will be limited if disk bandwidth becomes a bottleneck\nadmission.elastic_cpu.adjustment_delta_per_second\t0.001\tsets the per-second % adjustment used when when adapting elastic work CPU %s\nadmission.elastic_cpu.enabled\ttrue\twhen true, elastic work (like backups) performed by the KV layer is subject to admission control\nadmission.elastic_cpu.inactive_point\t0.1\tthe point between {min,max}_utilization the CPU % decreases to when there's no elastic work\nadmission.elastic_cpu.max_utilization\t0.75\tsets the ceiling on per-node elastic work CPU % utilization\nadmission.elastic_cpu.min_utilization\t0.05\tsets the floor on per-node elastic work CPU % utilization\nadmission.elastic_cpu.multiplicative_factor_on_decrease\t2\tsets the multiplier on negative adjustments to elastic work CPU %\nadmission.elastic_cpu.multiplicative_factor_on_inactive_decrease\t0.25\tsets the multiplier on negative adjustments to elastic work CPU % when inactive\nadmission.elastic_cpu.scheduler_latency_target\t1ms\tsets the p99 scheduling latency the elastic CPU controller aims for\nadmission.epoch_lifo.enabled\tfalse\twhen true, epoch-LIFO behavior is enabled when there is significant delay in admission\nadmission.epoch_lifo.epoch_closing_delta_duration\t5ms\tthe delta duration before closing an epoch, for epoch-LIFO admission control ordering\nadmission.epoch_lifo.epoch_duration\t100ms\tthe duration of an epoch, for epoch-LIFO admission control ordering\nadmission.epoch_lifo.queue_delay_threshold_to_switch_to_lifo\t105ms\tthe queue delay encountered by a (tenant,priority) for switching to epoch-LIFO ordering\nadmission.kv.bulk_only.enabled\tfalse\twhen both admission.kv.enabled and this is true, only throttle bulk work\nadmission.kv.enabled\ttrue\twhen true, work performed by the KV layer is subject to admission control\nadmission.kv.pause_replication_io_threshold\t0\tpause replication to non-essential followers when their I/O admission control score exceeds the given threshold (zero to disable)\nadmission.kv.stores.tenant_weights.enabled\tfalse\twhen true, tenant weights are enabled for KV-stores admission control\nadmission.kv.tenant_weights.enabled\tfalse\twhen true, tenant weights are enabled for KV admission control\nadmission.kv_slot_adjuster.overload_threshold\t32\twhen the number of runnable goroutines per CPU is greater than this threshold, the slot adjuster considers the cpu to be overloaded\nadmission.l0_file_count_overload_threshold\t1000\twhen the L0 file count exceeds this theshold, the store is considered overloaded\nadmission.l0_min_size_per_sub_level\t5242880\twhen non-zero, this indicates the minimum size that is needed to count towards one sub-level\nadmission.l0_sub_level_count_overload_threshold\t20\twhen the L0 sub-level count exceeds this threshold, the store is considered overloaded\nadmission.min_flush_util_fraction\t0.5\twhen computing flush tokens, this fraction is a lower bound on the dynamically adjusted flush utilization target fraction that attempts to reduce write stalls. Set it to a high fraction (>>1, e.g. 10), to disable flush based tokens. The dynamic target fraction is used to multiply the (measured) peak flush rate, to compute the flush tokens. If the storage.write-stall-nanos indicates significant write stalls, and the granter logs show that the dynamic target fraction has already reached the lower bound, one can consider lowering it slightly (after consultation with domain experts)\nadmission.replication_control.range_sequencer_gc_threshold\t5m0s\tthe inactive duration for a range sequencer after it's garbage collected\nadmission.sql_kv_response.enabled\ttrue\twhen true, work performed 