{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01QrXFwY22ogc2KjaUYYf6Pt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01W2q5fxke7WZBt1xUosiQEM","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat > /tmp/plan.md << 'EOF'\n# CockroachDB Minor-Version Upgrade Change Plan\n## v24.1.0 → v24.2.x\n\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-25\n**Status:** REVIEW ONLY — do not execute until approved in the change window.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current Cluster Inventory\n\n### 1.1 Version\n\n| Field | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Build Tag | v24.1.0 |\n| Build Time | 2024/05/15 21:28:29 |\n| Go Version | go1.22.2 |\n| Build Type | release (CCL) |\n| Platform | linux amd64 |\n\n### 1.2 StatefulSet & Pods\n\n| Field | Value |\n|---|---|\n| StatefulSet | crdb-cluster |\n| Namespace | cockroachdb |\n| Replicas | 3 (crdb-cluster-0, crdb-cluster-1, crdb-cluster-2) |\n| Container image | cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0 |\n| Update strategy | RollingUpdate (partition: 0) |\n| Pod management | Parallel |\n| terminationGracePeriodSeconds | 10 |\n| serviceAccount | crdb-cluster-sa |\n\n**Resource allocation per pod:**\n\n| Resource | Request | Limit |\n|---|---|---|\n| CPU | 1 | 1 |\n| Memory | 2Gi | 2Gi |\n\n**Startup flags:** `--insecure --advertise-host=<pod>.crdb-cluster.<ns>.svc.cluster.local --http-addr=0.0.0.0:8080 --port=26257 --cache=25% --max-sql-memory=25%`\n\n### 1.3 Storage\n\n| PVC | Bound Volume | Capacity | StorageClass |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| datadir-crdb-cluster-0 | pvc-484c8704-... | 10Gi | standard |\n| datadir-crdb-cluster-1 | pvc-38e6838d-... | 10Gi | standard |\n| datadir-crdb-cluster-2 | pvc-cc3aac95-... | 10Gi | standard |\n\nPVC retention policy: **Retain** on both scale-down and deletion.\n\n### 1.4 Services\n\n| Service | Type | Cluster-IP | Ports |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| crdb-cluster | ClusterIP (headless) | None | 26257/TCP, 8080/TCP |\n| crdb-cluster-public | ClusterIP | 10.96.210.224 | 26257/TCP, 8080/TCP |\n\n### 1.5 Node Topology\n\nAll 3 pods currently schedule on **karma-2-control-plane** (single node, single AZ).\nNo locality labels are set on the CockroachDB nodes.\n\n### 1.6 Databases\n\n| Database | Owner |\n|---|---|\n| defaultdb | root |\n| postgres | root |\n| system | node (internal) |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Non-Default Cluster Settings\n\nSettings that differ from the v24.1.0 shipped defaults:\n\n| Variable | Current Value | Default | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate` | **1.0 MiB** | 8.0 MiB | Throttled — limits rebalancing throughput. Will slow recovery after rolling restarts. |\n| `diagnostics.reporting.enabled` | **true** | false | Telemetry reporting is enabled. |\n| `cluster.secret` | `6a261902-...` | (auto) | Cluster identity token; set at init. No action required. |\n| `version` | **24.1** | (managed) | Finalized cluster version. Must be explicitly bumped to `24.2` post-upgrade. |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Zone Configuration Snapshot\n\nAll zones with explicitly configured values (captured via `crdb_internal.zones`):\n\n```sql\n-- Default range (user data)\nALTER RANGE default CONFIGURE ZONE USING\n  range_min_bytes = 134217728,   -- 128 MiB\n  range_max_bytes = 536870912,   -- 512 MiB\n  gc.ttlseconds   = 14400,       -- 4 h\n  num_replicas    = 3,\n  constraints     = '[]',\n  lease_preferences = '[]';\n\n-- System database\nALTER DATABASE system CONFIGURE ZONE USING\n  range_min_bytes = 134217728,\n  range_max_bytes = 536870912,\n  gc.ttlseconds   = 14400,\n  num_replicas    = 5,           -- WARNING: 5 replicas on a 3-node cluster → under-replicated\n  constraints     = '[]',\n  lease_preferences = '[]';\n\n-- Meta range\nALTER RANGE meta CONFIGURE ZONE USING\n  range_min_bytes = 134217728,\n  range_max_bytes = 536870912,\n  gc.ttlseconds   = 3600,        -- 1 h\n  num_replicas    = 5,           -- WARNING: under-replicated\n  constraints     = '[]',\n  lease_preferences = '[]';\n\n-- System range\nALTER RANGE system CONFIGURE ZONE USING\n  range_min_bytes = 134217728,\n  range_max_bytes = 536870912,\n  gc.ttlseconds   = 14400,\n  num_replicas    = 5,           -- WARNING: under-replicated\n  constraints     = '[]',\n  lease_preferences = '[]';\n\n-- Liveness range\nALTER RANGE liveness CONFIGURE ZONE USING\n  range_min_bytes = 134217728,\n  range_max_bytes = 536870912,\n  gc.ttlseconds   = 600,         -- 10 min\n  num_replicas    = 5,           -- WARNING: under-replicated\n  constraints     = '[]',\n  lease_preferences = '[]';\n\n-- System table overrides (GC only)\nALTER TABLE system.public.lease                          CONFIGURE ZONE USING gc.ttlseconds = 600;\nALTER TABLE system.public.replication_constraint_stats   CONFIGURE ZONE USING gc.ttlseconds = 600;\nALTER TABLE system.public.replication_stats              CONFIGURE ZONE USING gc.ttlseconds = 600;\nALTER TABLE system.public.statement_statistics           CONFIGURE ZONE USING gc.ttlseconds = 3600;\nALTER TABLE system.public.transaction_statistics         CONFIGURE ZONE USING gc.ttlseconds = 3600;\nALTER TABLE system.public.tenant_usage                   CONFIGURE ZONE USING gc.ttlseconds = 7200;\nALTER TABLE system.public.span_stats_tenant_boundaries   CONFIGURE ZONE USING gc.ttlseconds = 3600;\nALTER TABLE system.public.statement_activity             CONFIGURE ZONE USING gc.ttlseconds = 3600;\nALTER TABLE system.public.transaction_activity           CONFIGURE ZONE USING gc.ttlseconds = 3600;\n```\n\n> **Risk:** `system`, `meta`, `liveness`, and the `system` database zones request\n> **5 replicas** but the cluster has only 3 nodes. These ranges are perpetually\n> under-replicated. This should be resolved before the upgrade (see Pre-Flight\n> Checklist §5.1).\n\n---\n\n## 4. What Changes in v24.1 → v24.2\n\n### 4.1 Image Tag\n\n| Component | Before | After |\n|---|---|---|\n| StatefulSet `.spec.template.spec.containers[0].image` | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0` | `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.x` |\n\nReplace `x` with the latest patch on the v24.2 branch (e.g. `v24.2.5`).\nVerify the digest on [Docker Hub](https://hub.docker.com/r/cockroachdb/cockroach/tags)\nbefore the window.\n\n### 4.2 Cluster Version Finalization\n\nAfter all three pods are running the new binary, the cluster version must be\nmanually finalized:\n\n```sql\nSET CLUSTER SETTING version = '24.2';\n```\n\n**This step is irreversible.** Once finalized, the cluster cannot be rolled back\nto v24.1 without a full restore from backup.\n\n### 4.3 Kubernetes Manifest Changes\n\nOnly the `image:` field changes. All other manifest values remain as-is:\n\n```yaml\n# StatefulSet patch (kubectl apply or kubectl set image)\nspec:\n  template:\n    spec:\n      containers:\n      - name: db\n        image: cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.x   # ← only change\n```\n\n### 4.4 No Startup Flag Changes Required\n\nThe existing `--cache=25%` and `--max-sql-memory=25%` flags are valid in v24.2.\nNo additional or removed flags are required for this minor-version bump.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Pre-Flight Checklist\n\nVerify each item **before the maintenance window begins**:\n\n### 5.1 Resolve Under-Replicated Ranges (Recommended)\n\nThe `system`, `meta`, `liveness`, and `system` database zones are configured for\n5 replicas. With only 3 nodes these ranges are perpetually under-replicated,\nwhich means the cluster already tolerates fewer failures than intended. During a\nrolling restart, one node is temporarily unavailable; with under-replicated\nsystem ranges this further reduces quorum headroom.\n\n**Recommended action (run before the window, with team approval):**\n```sql\nALTER RANGE meta     CONFIGURE ZONE USING num_replicas = 3;\nALTER RANGE system   CONFIGURE ZONE USING num_replicas = 3;\nALTER RANGE liveness CONFIGURE ZONE USING num_replicas = 3;\nALTER DATABASE system CONFIGURE ZONE USING num_replicas = 3;\n```\n\nOr, if the intent is to scale to 5 nodes eventually, keep the zone configs and\ninstead add 2 more CockroachDB replicas to the StatefulSet before upgrading.\n\n### 5.2 Snapshot Rebalance Rate\n\n`kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate` is set to **1.0 MiB** (default: 8.0 MiB).\nThis will slow range rebalancing after each node restart. For a 10 Gi data\nvolume this is acceptable, but the rolling restart will take longer than with\nthe default rate.\n\nIf the maintenance window is time-constrained, consider temporarily raising the\nrate for the upgrade duration:\n```sql\nSET CLUSTER SETTING kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = '32 MiB';\n-- ... (restore after upgrade)\nSET CLUSTER SETTING kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = '1.0 MiB';\n```\n\n### 5.3 Pre-Upgrade Health Checks\n\n```bash\n# All 3 nodes live and available\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach node status --insecure\n\n# No under-replicated ranges\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SELECT range_id FROM crdb_internal.ranges_no_leases\n   WHERE array_length(replicas,1) < num_replicas LIMIT 5;\"\n\n# Current version confirmed\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING version;\"\n```\n\n### 5.4 Backup\n\nTake a full cluster backup before proceeding:\n```sql\nBACKUP INTO 's3://<bucket>/cockroachdb-pre-upgrade-v24.1.0/<timestamp>'\n  AS OF SYSTEM TIME '-10s';\n```\nAdjust the sink URI to match your backup target.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Upgrade Procedure\n\nCockroachDB rolling upgrades are performed one node at a time. The StatefulSet\n`RollingUpdate` strategy handles this automatically when the image is patched.\n\n### Step 1 — Patch the StatefulSet image\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb set image statefulset/crdb-cluster \\\n  db=cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.2.x\n```\n\nKubernetes will restart pods in reverse ordinal order:\n`crdb-cluster-2` → `crdb-cluster-1` → `crdb-cluster-0`.\n\n### Step 2 — Monitor the rollout\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb rollout status statefulset/crdb-cluster --watch\n```\n\nAfter each pod restarts, verify it re-joins the cluster before the next one\nis replaced:\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach node status --insecure\n```\nAll three nodes should show `is_live = true` between restarts.\n\n### Step 3 — Verify all nodes run v24.2\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach version\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-1 -- ./cockroach version\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-2 -- ./cockroach version\n```\n\nAll three must report `v24.2.x` before proceeding.\n\n### Step 4 — Finalize the cluster version (irreversible)\n\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SET CLUSTER SETTING version = '24.2';\"\n```\n\nConfirm:\n```bash\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SHOW CLUSTER SETTING version;\"\n```\n\nExpected output: `24.2`\n\n### Step 5 — Post-Upgrade Health Checks\n\n```bash\n# All nodes live\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach node status --insecure\n\n# No ranges under-replicated\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SELECT count(*) FROM crdb_internal.ranges_no_leases\n   WHERE array_length(replicas,1) < num_replicas;\"\n\n# Cluster settings preserved\nkubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- \\\n  ./cockroach sql --insecure -e \\\n  \"SELECT variable, value FROM crdb_internal.cluster_settings\n   WHERE value != default_value;\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. Rollback Plan\n\nRollback is **only possible before Step 4 (version finalization)**.\n\nIf a pod fails to start on v24.2 during the rolling update:\n\n```bash\n# Revert the image to v24.1.0\nkubectl -n cockroachdb set image statefulset/crdb-cluster \\\n  db=cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0\n\n# Monitor rollback\nkubectl -n cockroachdb rollout status statefulset/crdb-cluster --watch\n```\n\nAfter all nodes are back on v24.1.0, the cluster version (`24.1`) remains\nunchanged because Step 4 was never executed. The cluster is fully operational.\n\n**After Step 4 is executed, rollback requires restoring from the backup taken\nin §5.4.** There is no in-place downgrade path.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Risk Summary\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|---|---|---|\n| Under-replicated system/meta/liveness ranges during rolling restart | High | Align num_replicas=3 or add nodes before upgrade (§5.1) |\n| Version finalization is irreversible | High | Verify all nodes run v24.2 before executing §6 Step 4; take backup first |\n| Slow rebalancing due to throttled snapshot rate | Medium | Temporarily raise `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate` (§5.2) |\n| Single-AZ pod placement — one node failure during upgrade loses quorum | Medium | Acceptable for lab/staging; not for production without AZ spread |\n| `terminationGracePeriodSeconds = 10` may be too short for in-flight transactions | Low | Raise to 60s in the StatefulSet if needed; has no version dependency |\n| Insecure mode (no TLS) | Informational | Pre-existing; not changed by this upgrade |\n\n---\n\n## 9. Settings Preserved Post-Upgrade\n\nThese settings require no action; they survive the upgrade unchanged:\n\n- `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate = 1.0 MiB`\n- `diagnostics.reporting.enabled = true`\n- All zone configurations (gc.ttlseconds, num_replicas, range byte limits)\n- Startup flags (`--cache=25%`, `--max-sql-memory=25%`, `--insecure`)\n- PVC data (`whenDeleted: Retain`, `whenScaled: Retain`)\n\n---\n\n*End of change plan. This document is read-only. Submit edits via PR before the maintenance window.*\nEOF\necho \"plan.md written, $(wc -l < /tmp/plan.md) lines\"","description":"Write migration plan to /tmp/plan.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":769,"cache_read_input_tokens":36440,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":769},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier